         <div type="entry" xml:id="lc.jrn.1804-12-22.01" ref="">
            <sp who="wc">
               <speaker>Clark</speaker>
               <ab>
                  <date>
                     <hi rend="italic">22nd December Satturday 1804</hi>
                  </date>
               </ab>
               <p>a number of Squars womn &amp; men Dressed in Squars Clothes
          <ref target="n08122201" n="1"/>Came with Corn to Sell to the men for little things, we
          precured two horns of the animale the french Call the rock mountain Sheep [bighorn]
             those horns are not of the largest kind—    The 
          <name type="native_nation" key="Mandan Indians">mandans</name>Indians Call this Sheep 
          <hi rend="italic">Ar-Sar-ta</hi>   it is about the Size of a large Deer, or
          Small Elk, its Horns Come out and wind around the head like the horn of a Ram and the
          teckere [
          <hi rend="italic">NB: texture</hi>] not unlike it    much larger and thicker
          perticelarly that part with which they but or outer part which is [
          <hi rend="italic">blank</hi>] inchs thick, the length of those horns, which we have is
          <ref target="n08122202" n="2"/>
               </p>
            </sp>
         </div>
