        <hi rend="italic">bardache</hi>, a homosexual male, which 
        <name type="person" key="Clark, William">Clark</name>later and somewhat incorrectly
        explained to 
        <name type="person" key="Biddle, Nicholas">Biddle</name>that they were. 
        <name type="person" key="Biddle, Nicholas">Nicholas Biddle</name>Notes [ca. April 1810],
        Jackson (LLC), 2:531. Ronda (LCAI), 130–31, discusses the spiritual nature of this
        phenomenon, while Whitehead looks at the larger institution of gender-crossing.</note>
